13.3 Newtonâ€™s Law of Universal Gravitation
The force of gravity between any two objects:
\[F = G \frac{m_1 \cdot m_2}{r^2}\]
where \(G = 6.674 \times 10^{-11}\) Nâ‹…mÂ²/kgÂ², \(m_1\) and \(m_2\) are the masses, and \(r\) is the distance between them.


