13.3.1 ğŸ’¡ Why Orbits Change
An asteroidâ€™s orbit is stable as long as no outside forces act on it significantly. But orbits can change due to:

Gravitational perturbations â€” close passes by planets bend the orbit
Yarkovsky effect â€” sunlight heats one side, creating a tiny thrust
Collisions â€” impacts with other asteroids can redirect them
YORP effect â€” sunlight changes rotation rate, which changes orbit over time

This is why Apophisâ€™s 2029 flyby matters â€” Earthâ€™s gravity will bend its orbit, making future predictions harder.

