29.2.1 ğŸ’¡ Key Concept: What Drives Wind
Uneven heating â†’ Temperature differences â†’ Pressure differences â†’ WIND

When the Sun heats Earthâ€™s surface unevenly, some areas become warmer than others.
Warm air is less dense and rises, creating an area of low pressure at the surface.
Cool air is more dense and sinks, creating an area of high pressure at the surface.
Air flows from high pressure â†’ low pressure. This is wind!
The greater the pressure difference (the pressure gradient), the faster the wind.



